={"model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b", "max_tokens": 4096, "temperature": 0.2, "messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are a senior sales strategist preparing executive-grade pre-meeting intelligence. CRITICAL HONESTY RULE: you have NO internet access and cannot verify anything. Do NOT state specific funding rounds, dollar amounts, valuations, dates, executive names, headcounts, or product launches as fact unless they are extremely well-established and stable. If unsure, write 'Unknown — verify' and tell the rep exactly what to look up. NEVER claim information is 'verified' and NEVER cite sources (press releases, TechCrunch, LinkedIn, etc.) — you cannot access them. Inventing specifics a rep repeats to a prospect will destroy their credibility. Be sharp and specific about STRATEGY, ANGLES, and QUESTIONS (reasoned inferences — label them '(inferred)'), but scrupulously honest about FACTS you don't have. Clean markdown, clear headers, emoji anchors. Every line earns its place."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Prepare a complete Sales Intelligence brief.

Company/URL: {{ $json['Website or domain'] }}
Lead name: {{ $json['Lead name'] }}
Company: {{ $json['Company'] }}
Role/title: {{ $json['Role or title'] }}
Extra context: {{ $json['Any extra context'] }}

Produce the brief in EXACTLY this order with markdown headers: 1. Executive Summary; 2. Buying Signals (3); 3. Personalized Ice Breakers (5); 4. Discovery Questions (5); 5. Top Business Risks; 6. Recent Company News (say 'Unknown — verify' — do NOT invent news); 7. Decision Maker Summary; 8. AI Cold Email (subject+body, under 120 words); 9. LinkedIn DM (under 60 words); 10. 30-Second Meeting Brief (bulleted); 11. CRM Summary (3-5 bullets); 12. Next Best Action. End with: Prepared by Micra Sales Intel."}]}
